# ⚡ EduQuiz Arena — Full Stack Quiz Platform

**Dark Theme • Multiplayer • Real-time • XP System**

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
eduquiz/
├── frontend/
│   └── index.html          ← Complete React frontend (single file)
│
└── backend/
    ├── server.js           ← Node.js + Express + Socket.io backend
    ├── seed.js             ← Database seeder (sample questions)
    ├── package.json        ← Node.js dependencies
    └── .env.example        ← Environment variables template
```

---

## 🚀 Features

### ✅ Frontend (React + HTML + CSS)
| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| 🏠 Landing Page | Hero section with stats, features grid, CTA buttons |
| 🔐 Auth Pages | Login & Signup with animated form |
| 📊 Dashboard | Stats cards, subject progress, live rooms preview |
| 📝 Solo Quiz | Subject selection, timer, instant feedback, XP rewards |
| ⚔️ Multiplayer | Room list, create room, lobby, real-time quiz battle |
| 🏆 Leaderboard | Weekly/Monthly/All-time rankings |
| 👤 Profile | XP, level, achievements, subject stats |
| 📋 History | Past quiz attempts with scores |

### ✅ Backend (Node.js + Express + MongoDB + Socket.io)
| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| 🔐 Auth API | Register, Login, JWT tokens, streak tracking |
| ❓ Questions API | CRUD, subject filter, difficulty, user submission |
| 📊 Quiz API | Submit answers, calculate XP, save results |
| 🏆 Leaderboard API | Weekly/monthly/all-time aggregation |
| 🏠 Rooms API | Create/list multiplayer rooms |
| ⚡ Real-time Socket | Join room, ready up, submit answer, live scores, chat |
| 👮 Admin Routes | Approve questions, manage users |

---

## ⚙️ Backend Setup

### 1. Install Dependencies
```bash
cd backend
npm install
```

### 2. Configure Environment
```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your MongoDB URI and JWT secret
```

### 3. Start MongoDB
```bash
# Local MongoDB
mongod

# OR use MongoDB Atlas (cloud) — update MONGO_URI in .env
```

### 4. Seed the Database
```bash
node seed.js
# Adds 22 sample questions across 6 subjects
```

### 5. Start the Server
```bash
npm run dev     # Development (with nodemon)
npm start       # Production
```

Server runs at: `http://localhost:5000`

---

## 🌐 API Reference

### Auth
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Create account |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login & get token |
| GET | `/api/auth/me` | Get current user |

### Quiz
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/questions?subject=Math&difficulty=Medium` | Fetch questions |
| POST | `/api/questions` | Submit a question |
| POST | `/api/quiz/submit` | Submit quiz answers |
| GET | `/api/quiz/history` | User quiz history |
| GET | `/api/quiz/stats` | User statistics |

### Leaderboard
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/leaderboard?period=weekly` | Get rankings |

### Multiplayer
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/api/rooms` | List open rooms |
| POST | `/api/rooms` | Create a room |

---

## 🔌 Socket.io Events

### Client → Server
| Event | Payload | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `join_room` | `{ roomCode, playerName }` | Join a multiplayer room |
| `player_ready` | — | Signal ready to start |
| `start_game` | — | Host starts the game |
| `submit_answer` | `{ questionIndex, answer, timeTaken }` | Submit answer |
| `chat_message` | `{ message }` | Send chat message |

### Server → Client
| Event | Payload | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `joined` | Room info + players | Successfully joined |
| `room_update` | Players list + phase | Player joined/left/readied |
| `question` | Question data (no answer) | New question starts |
| `timer_tick` | `{ timeLeft }` | Countdown per question |
| `score_update` | All player scores | Someone answered |
| `question_end` | Correct answer + scores | Question time up |
| `game_end` | Final scores + winner | Game finished |
| `chat_message` | `{ name, message, time }` | Chat broadcast |
| `error` | `{ msg }` | Error message |

---

## 🔌 Frontend ↔ Backend Integration

To connect the React frontend to the backend, add these to your `index.html`:

```html
<!-- Socket.io client -->
<script src="http://localhost:5000/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
```

```javascript
// Connect socket
const socket = io('http://localhost:5000', {
  auth: { token: localStorage.getItem('token') }
});

// Join a room
socket.emit('join_room', { roomCode: 'QUIZ01', playerName: 'Rahul' });

// Listen for questions
socket.on('question', (data) => { /* render question */ });

// Submit answer
socket.emit('submit_answer', { questionIndex: 0, answer: 2, timeTaken: 8 });
```

